reference "eq:EntropyConditionForSystem"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 must be satisfied.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 characteristic fields, so the initial discontinuity will be carried by
 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 elementary waves, each of which might be a shock wave, a rarefaction wave,
 or a contact discontinuity.
 A shock wave or a rarefaction wave can only occur in a genuinely nonlinear
 field, while a contact discontinuity can only occur in a linearly degenerated
 field.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Based on these facts, we claim that:
\end_layout

